Fix IBEX 2.7.4 with GCC 15.

IBEX's Waf files unconditionally add -U__STRICT_ANSI__ as an old workaround
for Windows builds.  With GCC 15's libstdc++ this breaks standard headers such
as <limits>.  Filib also needs fenv declarations when its interval headers are
included by consumers.

diff --git a/plugins/operators/src/ibex_atanhc.h b/plugins/operators/src/ibex_atanhc.h
